- Wayland: some global shortcut or low-level APIs may not work depending on compositor (GNOME/Wayland may restrict global shortcuts). Menu accelerators are usually more reliable.
- Desktop environment: the DE might have bound F11 itself (e.g., toggling the terminal fullscreen). If the DE captures it first, you‚Äôll need a different accelerator or ask users to unbind the DE shortcut.
- Input focus: if a focused input consumes the keydown, the document listener might not see it.
