Details ‚Äî JS clipboard copy (browser)
- Modern, secure-context method (async):

```js
// Modern (HTTPS / localhost)
async function copyToClipboard(text) {
  try {
    await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
    console.log('Copied to clipboard');
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Failed to copy: ', err);
    // optionally fallback here
  }
}
```

- Optional permission check (not always necessary; write usually allowed with user gesture):

```js
async function canWriteClipboard() {
  try {
    const status = await navigator.permissions.query({ name: 'clipboard-write' });
    return status.state === 'granted' || status.state === 'prompt';
  } catch (e) {
    // Permissions API not supported in all browsers
    return true;
  }
}
```

- Fallback for older browsers:

```js
function fallbackCopyTextToClipboard(text) {
  const el = document.createElement('textarea');
  el.value = text;
  // avoid scrolling to bottom
  el.setAttribute('readonly', '');
  el.style.position = 'absolute';
  el.style.left = '-9999px';
  document.body.appendChild(el);
  el.select();
  try {
    document.execCommand('copy'); // deprecated but widely supported
    console.log('Fallback: copied');
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('Fallback: unable to copy', err);
  }
  document.body.removeChild(el);
}
```

- Combined helper:

```js
async function safeCopy(text) {
  if (navigator.clipboard && navigator.clipboard.writeText) {
    try {
      await navigator.clipboard.writeText(text);
      return true;
    } catch (_) {
      // fall through to fallback
    }
  }
  fallbackCopyTextToClipboard(text);
  return false;
}
```

Notes:
- navigator.clipboard.writeText requires HTTPS or localhost and often a user gesture (click or keypress).
- Reading from clipboard (navigator.clipboard.readText) has tighter permissions and may require explicit user consent.
- Test across the browsers you target; modern Chromium/Firefox/Safari support the writeText API on secure contexts.

